{
  "stem": "10353.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't know what happened to anybody.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were in there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we couldn't-- from time to time, they would take us out to work, either to clean the gutters or to go out in the woods to chop wood for the kitchen.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- But most of the day you just stayed in the barracks?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We-- we sort of worked around the camp.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We cleaned up.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We we weren't-- we weren't in charge of any real heavy physical work.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But every morning, the women who were on the other side of the camp, they were mostly in the red barracks, they were marched-- there was a weaving factory adjacent to our camp, which was adjacent to the crematoria.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They would be marching through on the main road of the camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And all of a sudden, somebody yelled-- somebody came and told me that the women would be marched by SS women, surrounded or guarded by SS women with dogs and-- but they would be yelling out names, you know.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Wherever you went and you saw a group of people, you would be yelling out names.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Maybe you would find somebody.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the boys in my barrack came and told me-- because they would be standing at the gates, you know, that was wired, electrically wired-- that they heard that one girl called my name.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So the following day I went out and I yelled out, who called my name?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was mostly Hungarian women-- not mostly, but all of them were Hungarian women.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Columns upon columns were going to work.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And sure enough, it was a girl that I knew from my home town, was my girlfriend.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we made a connection and we started to trade a little bit.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
